item.title: Neutron(supposed to be :p)
item.dc:creator: @ThAt0n36Uy Elijah
item.description:
@ThAt0n36Uy wrote:

Wow, you’re cool, you can make a black background with some pictures on it, with a nice bit of text. All you did was take a C4D or something and place it in the background, take a render, duplicate it, set it to motion blur on 120%, and add some text with outer glow.

The neutron is pretty bad quality. The circles and other shapes have white edges around them. The white background is very distracting in it. All in all it was a nice shot at making an atom. But the quality is very bad. Most people wouldn’t sit there and take the time to make something like that from scratch, if you in fact did.

2/10
